
You know of the following tools.  Select which of the following tools you will
need to accomplish the task and add them to the **Tools Needed** section of the 
ftl-document.

* apt_tool - Control apt packages
* authorized_key_tool - Manage authorized keys and upload public keys to the remote node
* bash_tool - Run a bash script
* chmod_tool - Changes the permissions of a file or directory.
* chown_tool - Changes the ownership of a directory and the files in it. 
* copy_tool - Copy file to remote machine
* copy_from_tool - Copy file from remote machine locally
* discord_tool - Sends a message to discord.
* dnf_tool - Control dnf packages
* firewalld_tool - Configure firewalld
* get_url_tool - Downloads a file
* git_tool - Deploy software from git checkouts
* hostname_tool - Sets the hostname of the machine.
* java_jar_tool - Run a java jar 
* lineinfile_tool - Add a line to a file
* linode_tool - Provisions a new linode server
* mkdir_tool - Make a directory on the remote machine
* pip_tool - Install python packages using pip 
* pip_requirements_tool - Install dependencies from python requirements.txt files using pip.
* service_tool - Manager a service
* slack_tool - Sends a message to slack.
* swapfile_tool - Creates a swapfile
* systemd_service_tool - Control systemd services
* timezone_tool - Configure timezone setting
* unarchive_tool - Unarchives files from the archive file to the destination directory.
* user_tool - Create a user
